SIMPLE: importunate
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Importunate
<hw>Im*por"tu*nate</hw> <pr>(⟦icr⟧m*p⟦ocir⟧r"t⟦usl⟧*n⟦asl⟧t)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Importune</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Troublesomely urgent; unreasonably solicitous; overpressing in
request or demand; urgent; teasing; <as>as, an <ex>importunate</ex>
petitioner, curiosity</as>.</def> <rj><au>Whewell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hard to be borne; unendurable.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Donne.</au></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Im*por"tu*nate*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Im*por"tu*nate*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Importunator</ent>⟦br⟧
